    <h2 id="why-immune">The Science Behind Immune Support Supplements</h2>

    <p>Your immune system is not a single organ — it is a complex network of cells, proteins, tissues, and signaling molecules that requires specific nutritional inputs to function properly. White blood cells (lymphocytes, neutrophils, macrophages) need zinc to develop, vitamin C to protect against oxidative damage during pathogen killing, and vitamin D to activate toll-like receptors that detect and respond to infections. When any of these nutrients is deficient, immune response measurably deteriorates.</p>

