        <p>Vitamin D activates toll-like receptors on immune cells and stimulates antimicrobial peptide production. A BMJ meta-analysis of 25 RCTs found D supplementation reduced acute respiratory infections by 12% overall and 70% in severely deficient individuals. The most impactful single nutrient for immune defense.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="info-card">
