    <!-- FAQ SECTION -->
    <h2 id="faq">Frequently Asked Questions About Immune Gummies</h2>

    <details class="fq">
      <summary>Do immune gummies actually work?</summary>
      <p>Yes, when they contain clinically studied ingredients at effective doses. Vitamin D reduces respiratory infections by 12-70% depending on baseline status. Zinc reduces cold duration by 33% when taken early. Elderberry shortens upper respiratory symptoms by an average of 2 days. The key is choosing products with adequate dosing of evidence-backed ingredients rather than trendy botanicals at fairy-dust amounts.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="fq">
      <summary>What is the best ingredient for immune support?</summary>
      <p>Vitamin D is the most impactful for the general population because 42% of Americans are deficient. Zinc is the second priority for immune cell development. Vitamin C supports immune cell function and acts as an antioxidant shield. Elderberry provides antiviral anthocyanins. The best immune gummies combine multiple ingredients for multi-pathway support.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="fq">
      <summary>Should I take immune gummies year-round?</summary>
      <p>Yes. Vitamin D takes 8-12 weeks to replete from deficiency, and zinc stores build gradually. Starting supplementation only when sick misses the preventive window. Daily year-round use maintains the nutrient levels your immune system needs at all times, with optional dose increases during peak cold and flu season.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="fq">
      <summary>Can I take elderberry, vitamin C, and zinc together?</summary>
      <p>Yes. These ingredients work through different immune pathways and can be safely combined. Elderberry provides anthocyanin antioxidants, vitamin C supports neutrophil function, and zinc builds immune cells. Many top products combine all three. Just avoid exceeding the Tolerable Upper Intake Level for zinc (40mg/day) or vitamin C (2000mg/day).</p>
    </details>

    <details class="fq">
      <summary>How much vitamin C do I need for immune support?</summary>
      <p>200mg daily achieves near-saturation of plasma and immune cell vitamin C levels. Doses above 200mg produce minimal additional benefit in healthy individuals. During active illness, 500-1000mg may help because immune cells consume vitamin C rapidly. Mega-doses above 2000mg cause GI distress and kidney stone risk without additional immune benefit.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="fq">
      <summary>Is elderberry safe to take every day?</summary>
      <p>Properly processed elderberry extract (like Sambucol) is safe for daily use. Commercial extracts are heat-treated to eliminate cyanogenic glycosides found in raw berries. Consult your healthcare provider if you have an autoimmune condition or take immunosuppressive medications due to elderberry's theoretical cytokine-stimulating potential.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="fq">
      <summary>Do immune gummies help prevent COVID?</summary>
      <p>No supplement prevents COVID-19. However, adequate vitamin D status is associated with reduced COVID severity (3.7-fold reduced risk of severe outcomes in one meta-analysis), and zinc supports antiviral immune responses. Immune gummies support optimal immune function rather than targeting specific pathogens.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="fq">
      <summary>What is the difference between elderberry and echinacea?</summary>
      <p>Elderberry has stronger clinical evidence for respiratory infection duration and severity. A 2019 meta-analysis confirmed elderberry's benefits. Echinacea's evidence is more mixed — a 2014 Cochrane review found limited support. Elderberry is our recommended botanical for immune gummies.</p>
    </details>

